# Khpyuk, Suleyman-Stalsky District, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Khpyuk (; ) is a rural locality (a selo) in Suleyman-Stalsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. Population:  There are 3 streets.
Geography
Khpyuk is located 21&nbsp;km west of Kasumkent (the district's administrative centre) by road. Kachalkent is the nearest rural locality.
